lifications and the capacity to provide the services and meet the requirements under the contract the Native Hawaiian health care system enters into with the Secretary or the grant the Native Hawaiian health care system receives from the Secretary pursuant to this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf57daf5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11711/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Papa Ola Lokahi","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf57daf6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11711/7/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Papa Ola Lokahi” means an organization composed of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf57daf7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11711/7/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" E Ola Mau;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf57daf8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11711/7/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Office of Hawaiian Affairs of the State of Hawaii;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf57daf9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11711/7/A/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Alu Like Inc.;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf57dafa-3a70-